<paragraph blockId="82.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis box="[199,297,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Remarks</emphasis>
. The species was considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[873,1047,152,175]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Chonosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipennis">
<emphasis box="[873,1047,152,175]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">C. crassipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[1092,1273,151,176]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" refId="ref71233" refString="Distant, W. L. (1906 b) A synonymic catalogue of Homoptera. Part I. Cicadidae. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 207 pp. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8554" type="book" year="1906">Distant (1906b)</bibRefCitation>
. However, the species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[389,565,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Chonosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipennis">
<emphasis box="[389,565,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">C. crassipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in several ways. The opercula of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berg" authorityYear="1882" box="[966,1058,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tettigades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papa">
<emphasis box="[966,1058,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">C. papa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are larger with a medial margin smoothly arching towards the midline beyond the medial meracanthus while the opercula of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[1218,1392,224,247]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Chonosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipennis">
<emphasis box="[1218,1392,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">C. crassipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more angulate on the medial margin and does not extend medially to the meracanthus; the uncus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berg" authorityYear="1882" box="[1259,1347,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tettigades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papa">
<emphasis box="[1259,1347,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">C. papa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more stout along with a larger basal lobe of the pygofer and longer anal styles. Females are distinguished by the notch on the posterior of sternite 
<collectionCode box="[427,466,332,355]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">VII</collectionCode>
which has parallel sides posteriorly with a circular anterior terminus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Berg" authorityYear="1882" box="[1296,1386,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tettigades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papa">
<emphasis box="[1296,1386,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">C. papa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and expands anteriorly into a tear-drop shape in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[647,820,368,391]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Chonosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipennis">
<emphasis box="[647,820,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">C. crassipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sanborn &amp; Heath" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Berg" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[835,1005,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Chonosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papa">
<emphasis box="[835,1005,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Chonosia papa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also has a more southerly distribution with examples being reported from 
<collectingRegion box="[556,638,404,429]" country="Argentina" name="Chubut" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Chubut</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[694,798,404,429]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Mendoza</collectingRegion>
Provinces (
<bibRefCitation author="Berg, C." box="[932,1055,404,429]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" pagination="38 - 48" refId="ref69870" refString="Berg, C. (1882) Contribuciones al estudio, de las Cicadidae de la Republica Argentina y paises limitrofes. Anales de la Sociedad Cientifica Argentina, 14, 38 - 48." type="journal article" year="1882">Berg 1882</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Breddin, G." box="[1067,1225,404,429]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref70154" refString="Breddin, G. (1897) Hemipteren. Ergbnisse der Hamburger Magalhaesischen Sammelreise 1892 / 93. Herausgegeben vom Naturhistorischen Museum zu Hamburg, 2, 1 - 38, plate 1." type="journal article" year="1897">Breddin 1897</bibRefCitation>
). We collected our examples in 
<collectingRegion box="[292,505,439,464]" country="Argentina" name="Mendoza" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">Mendoza Province</collectingRegion>
. The species is associated with the Monte floristic province (
<bibRefCitation author="Sanborn, A. F. &amp; Heath, J. E. &amp; Phillips, P. K. &amp; Heath, M. S. &amp; Noriega, F. G." box="[1182,1418,439,464]" pageId="82" pageNumber="83" pagination="29368" refId="ref75044" refString="Sanborn, A. F., Heath, J. E., Phillips, P. K., Heath, M. S. &amp; Noriega, F. G. (2011 a) Thermal adaptation and diversity in tropical ecosystems: evidence from cicadas (Hemiptera, Cicadidae). PLoS ONE, 6 (12), e 29368. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0029368" type="journal article" year="2011">
Sanborn 
<emphasis box="[1284,1340,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="82" pageNumber="83">et al.</emphasis>
2011a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
